      • AdjacencyMatrix

        public AdjacencyMatrix(boolean trackCommonNeighbors)
        Creates a new empty adjacency matrix.
        Parameters:
        trackCommonNeighbors - Indicates if this matrix caches common neighbors of vertices during insertion and removal of edges. The method getCommonNeighbors(int, int) requires this switch to be set to true.

      • synchronizeEdges

        public <G extends Graph,E extends Edge> void synchronizeEdges(G g,
                                                              GraphBuilder<G,V,E> builder)
        Synchronizes the edges of an existing graph with the same set of vertices with the edges of this matrix. This method will fail if either the number of vertices of this matrix or the set of vertices of the graph has changed since the construction of this matrix.
        Type Parameters:
        G - the type parameter of the graph.
        E - the type parameter of the edges.
        Parameters:
        g - a graph with the same set of vertices.
        builder - a graph builder to add and remove edges to the graph.
